Eighth Avenue, west side, fromm 33rd to 35th Streets, showing Printing Crafts Building and Hotel New Yorker. U. S. Navy birigible 'Los Angeles' overhead.

712060f-a.text:
W. 33rd Street (from left to right), north side, between Ninth and Eighth Avenues, as viewed northeastward across a corner of the railroad yards at the rear of the Post Office (low structure partially shown at the right). The photographer has a vantage point on W. 32nd Street to the west of Ninth Avenue (which does not appear) and shows the West Side area comprising Manhattans' vast garment area that concentrates around Eighth Avenue.
December 20, 1930.
P.L. Sperr

731320f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - W.P.A. [Works Progress Administration] Parade.
731320f-a.text:
(1)
A portion of the W.P.A. protest parade, held to make demands for
more appropriations and other concessions on the government's part, as
seen from 33rd 5trect and Eighth Ave. The general Post Office may be seen in the background. The marchers shown, are the W.P.A. Teachers contingent.
January 9, 1937.
Geo, D. Chinn.
(2)
The childrens Theatre group in the same parade; seen from the same location.
January 9, 1937.
Geo. D. Chinn.
